		<item>
		<title>Immigration orders on hold, Egypt requests assistance and more in today&#8217;s Briefing.</title>
		<link>http://briefi.ng/02-17-2015/549</link>
		<comments>http://briefi.ng/02-17-2015/549#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 17 Feb 2015 12:24:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[wvnutt]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Daily Briefing]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://briefi.ng/?p=549</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Crosshairs Fixed on Libya Egypt is calling for an international coalition to fight terrorist forces gaining ground in Libya. The diplomatic push came hours after the Egyptian Air Force bombed an ISIS base in Libya, the largest foothold for the terrorist group outside of Iraq and Syria. The bombings were in response to the video [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="row dark" id="s1">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Crosshairs Fixed on Libya </h1>
<p>Egypt is calling for an <a href="http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/M/ML_ISLAMIC_STATE?SITE=AP&#038;SECTION=HOME&#038;TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&#038;CTIME=2015-02-16-13-11-09" target="_blank">international coalition</a> to fight terrorist forces gaining ground in Libya.</p>
<p>The diplomatic push came hours after the Egyptian Air Force bombed an ISIS base in Libya, the <a href="http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/M/ML_ISLAMIC_STATE_QA?SITE=AP&#038;SECTION=HOME&#038;TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&#038;CTIME=2015-02-16-13-30-35" target="_blank">largest foothold</a> for the terrorist group outside of Iraq and Syria. The bombings were in response to the video of <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/17/world/middleeast/isis-egypt-libya-airstrikes.html?_r=0" target="_blank">ISIS’s beheading</a> of 21 Coptic Christians from Egypt, released Sunday.</p>
<p>Egyptian President Abdel-Fattah el-Sisi is arguing that Libya’s deterioration is as urgent as the crises facing Iraq and Syria. And his reasoning isn’t just in reaction to the beheadings; Egypt is also battling a militant group in the Sinai Peninsula—located along Egypt&#8217;s northeastern border with Israel—that has sworn allegiance to ISIS.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/02/16/egypt-islamic-state_n_6690262.html" target="_blank"><img class="huffpo" src="http://briefi.ng/media/huffpo.svg"></a><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/17/world/middleeast/isis-egypt-libya-airstrikes.html?_r=0" target="_blank"><img class="nyt" src="http://briefi.ng/media/nyt.svg"></a><a href="http://www.wsj.com/articles/egypt-strikes-islamic-state-targets-in-libya-1424071790" target="_blank"><img class="wsj last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/wsj.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row" id="s2">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Orders on Hold</h1>
<p>President Obama’s executive actions were  <a href="http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2015/02/17/federal-judge-temporarily-blocks-obama-immigration-executive-action/" target="_blank">temporarily blocked</a> Monday by a federal judge in Texas.</p>
<p>Last year, Obama announced a number of immigration orders that would allow up to 5 million undocumented immigrants to remain in the U.S. Some of the orders were set to take effect Wednesday.</p>
<p>But U.S. District Judge Andrew Hanen agreed with a coalition of 26 states that said the orders violate the U.S. Constitution. The White House shot back Tuesday, saying it expects the Department of Justice to  <a href="http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_IMMIGRATION_LAWSUIT?SITE=AP&#038;SECTION=HOME&#038;TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&#038;CTIME=2015-02-17-03-19-57" target="_blank">appeal the decision</a>.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://news.yahoo.com/federal-judge-stalls-obamas-executive-action-immigration-052549363.html" target="_blank"><img class="yahoo" src="http://briefi.ng/media/yahoo.svg"></a><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/18/us/obama-immigration-policy-halted-by-federal-judge-in-texas.html" target="_blank"><img class="nyt" src="http://briefi.ng/media/nyt.svg"></a><a href="http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/federal-judge-texas-blocks-president-obamas-executive-action/story?id=29011861" target="_blank"><img class="abc last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/abc.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row dark" id="s3">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Greece Going Alone?</h1>
<p>On Monday, Greece responded to the European Union’s (EU) offer to extend the country’s $272.2 billion bailout by six months with: <a href="http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/17/us-eurozone-greece-idUSKBN0LJ0SH20150217" target="_blank">No.</a></p>
<p>Greek Prime Minister Alexis Tsipras told the EU last week that the debt-ridden country wouldn’t abide by the bailout’s austerity requirements. Monday’s rejection of the proposal <a href="http://www.wsj.com/articles/germanys-schauble-skeptical-on-reaching-deal-on-greek-bailout-1424087492" target="_blank">redoubled fears</a> that Greece will eventually leave the EU, which would almost certainly destabilize the euro and damage the global economy.</p>
<p>In response to Monday’s failed negotiations, the EU told Greece it has until the end of the week to reach an agreement. Finance Minister Yanis Varoufakis said the Greek government is willing to &#8220;<a href="http://www.cbsnews.com/news/greece-still-struggling-to-clinch-new-bailout/" target="_blank">do whatever it takes</a>” to find a solution.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.cbsnews.com/news/greece-still-struggling-to-clinch-new-bailout/" target="_blank"><img class="cbsnews" src="http://briefi.ng/media/cbsnews.svg"></a><a href="http://www.wsj.com/articles/germanys-schauble-skeptical-on-reaching-deal-on-greek-bailout-1424087492" target="_blank"><img class="wsj" src="http://briefi.ng/media/wsj.svg"></a><a href="http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/greece-creditors-debt-talks-28994036" target="_blank"><img class="abc last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/abc.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
