<div class="row" id="s4">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Money Icon Icahn Talks Money</h1>
<p>Apple stock should be worth $216/share, not $124/share, billionaire Carl Icahn said in a <a href="http://www.shareholderssquaretable.com/letter-to-twitter-followers-regarding-apple" target="_blank">letter to his Twitter</a> followers Wednesday.</p>
<p>Icahn’s stock estimate would put Apple’s <a href="http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/12/us-apple-icahn-idUSKBN0LF2EU20150212" target="_blank">valuation at over $1 trillion</a>, a convenient proposition for a guy who owns 53 million Apple shares worth about $6.5 billion. Apple’s current valuation is around $700 billion.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2015/02/11/carl-icahn-apple-tim-cook/23242719/" target="_blank"><img class="usatoday" src="http://briefi.ng/media/usatoday.svg"></a><a href="http://www.forbes.com/fdc/welcome_mjx.shtml" target="_blank"><img class="forbes" src="http://briefi.ng/media/forbes.svg"></a><a href="http://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2015/02/11/icahn-presses-apple-to-buy-back-more-shares-again/" target="_blank"><img class="wsj last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/wsj.svg"></a>
                      </div>
