		<item>
		<title>Gay weddings go South, Obama and Merkel talk peace and more in today’s Briefing.</title>
		<link>http://briefi.ng/02-10-2015/467</link>
		<comments>http://briefi.ng/02-10-2015/467#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 10 Feb 2015 12:44:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[wvnutt]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Daily Briefing]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://briefi.ng/?p=467</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Gettin’ Hitched Alabama became the 37th state to (*mostly*) allow gay marriage Monday. The *mostly* stemmed from Alabama Chief Justice Roy Moore, who ordered probate judges not to issue gay marriage licenses. A few counties either submitted to the order or closed their licensing facilities altogether. But marriage licenses were issued in several cities, including [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="row dark" id="s1">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Gettin’ Hitched</h1>
<p>Alabama became the 37th state to (*mostly*) allow gay marriage Monday.</p>
<p>The *mostly* stemmed from Alabama Chief Justice Roy Moore, who ordered probate judges not to issue gay marriage licenses. A few counties either submitted to the order or closed their licensing facilities altogether. But marriage licenses were <a href="http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_GAY_MARRIAGE_ALABAMA?SITE=AP&#038;SECTION=HOME&#038;TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&#038;CTIME=2015-02-09-17-47-18" target="_blank">issued in several cities</a>, including Birmingham and Montgomery.</p>
<p>The controversy <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/10/us/justice-thomass-dissent-hints-of-supreme-courts-intentions-on-same-sex-marriage.html?_r=0" target="_blank">spilled over into the Supreme Court</a>, too. The high court denied a motion to block Alabama’s issuance of gay marriage licenses Monday. That prompted a stern dissent from Justices Clarence Thomas and Antonin Scalia.</p>
<p>Thomas said Alabama’s current law should’ve remained in place, since the court will ultimately decide whether there’s a constitutional right to gay marriage later this year. The court <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/courts_law/supreme-court-refuses-to-hold-back-alabama-same-sex-marriages/2015/02/09/203d8494-b06b-11e4-854b-a38d13486ba1_story.html" target="_blank">will hear cases</a> in April from Kentucky, Michigan, Ohio, and Tennessee, which have upheld traditional marriage.</p>
<p>The court’s “indecorous” decision “may well be seen as a signal of the court’s intended resolution of that question,” wrote Thomas.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/alabama-judge-stakes-out-defiant-stance-against-same-sex-marriages/2015/02/09/a1be2de4-b06f-11e4-854b-a38d13486ba1_story.html?hpid=z1" target="_blank"><img class="wapo" src="http://briefi.ng/media/wapo.svg"></a><a href="http://abcnews.go.com/US/alabama-37th-state-sex-marriages/story?id=28836644" target="_blank"><img class="abc" src="http://briefi.ng/media/abc.svg"></a><a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/michelangelo-signorile/meet-alabama-chief-justic_b_6646030.html" target="_blank"><img class="huffpo last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/huffpo.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row" id="s2">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Waiting for Wednesday</h1>
<p>President Obama <a href="http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_UKRAINE_DIPLOMACY?SITE=AP&#038;SECTION=HOME&#038;TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&#038;CTIME=2015-02-09-18-30-10">hasn’t decided</a> whether to send military aid to Ukraine, but in the meantime, he’s hoping German Chancellor Angela Merkel cuts a peace deal with Russia and Ukraine.</p>
<p>Obama and Merkel held a joint press conference at the White House Monday, with Obama reiterating the administration’s criticism of Russian aggression in eastern Ukraine. For her part, Merkel continued to oppose all talk of foreign military aid to Ukraine. Russian President Vladimir Putin has denied—<i>ahem, lied</i>—any direct involvement in the conflict, which has left more than 5,300 people dead since April.</p>
<p>Putin and Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko will meet with Merkel and French President Francois Hollande in Minsk, Belarus Wednesday to discuss a possible truce. Let’s hope it works.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.cbsnews.com/news/merkel-says-ukraine-conflict-cannot-be-solved-militarily/" target="_blank"><img class="cbsnews" src="http://briefi.ng/media/cbsnews.svg"></a><a href="http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2015/02/09/384943451/ukraine-likely-to-top-obama-merkel-talks-agenda" target="_blank"><img class="npr" src="http://briefi.ng/media/npr.svg"></a><a href="http://edition.cnn.com/2015/02/09/europe/ukraine-conflict/index.html" target="_blank"><img class="cnn last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/cnn.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row dark" id="s3">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Asking for Permission &#8230; For What You Already Did</h1>
<p>President Obama is expected to ask Congress for broader authority in the U.S.-led airstrikes against ISIS … which began six-months ago.</p>
<p>Obama’s request is <a href="http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/02/10/us-mideast-crisis-congress-idUSKBN0LD29U20150210">expected Wednesday</a> and would provide Congress with its first vote on a war that has escalated on both sides. ISIS has continued its campaign of shock-inducing, propaganda-minded executions; U.S. coalition forces have responded with more bombs.</p>
<p>After ISIS’s caged immolation of a Jordanian pilot last month, Jordan expanded its bombing operations to Iraq. The Jordanians said Sunday that they had conducted <a href="http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2015/02/jordan-bombed-isil-56-times-days-150208133049169.html">56 airstrikes in three days</a>. Now, U.S.-backed Iraqi forces <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/in-battle-against-islamic-state-iraqi-cities-loom--and-are-treacherous/2015/02/08/0439cf3e-ad76-11e4-abe8-e1ef60ca26de_story.html">are preparing</a> for the bloody task of fighting ISIS in urban cities like Mosul and Fallujah.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/02/09/us/politics/ap-us-congress-war-powers.html" target="_blank"><img class="nyt" src="http://briefi.ng/media/nyt.svg"></a><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/obama-send-war-powers-request-capitol-hill-080650512--politics.html" target="_blank"><img class="yahoo" src="http://briefi.ng/media/yahoo.svg"></a><a href="http://edition.cnn.com/2015/02/09/politics/isis-war-obama-permission/" target="_blank"><img class="cnn last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/cnn.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row" id="s4">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>More Snow, Yo</h1>
<p>Boston was blasted again Monday, <a href="http://www.usatoday.com/story/weather/2015/02/09/boston-new-england-snow-records/23109017/">getting 22 inches of snow</a>. Massachusetts Gov. Charlie Baker declared a state of emergency and asked for neighboring states to help with snow removal.</p>
<p>Boston has accumulated more than 71 inches of snow in the last 30-days, smashing its previous record of 58 inches. What’s worse? Two <a href="http://www.weather.com/storms/winter/news/more-northeast-snow-valentines-weekend">more storms are expected</a> to hit New England later this week.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2015/02/09/384914377/snow-hits-the-northeast-again-as-pacific-storms-bring-floods-to-the-west" target="_blank"><img class="npr" src="http://briefi.ng/media/npr.svg"></a><a href="http://abcnews.go.com/US/boston-snow-storm-facts-show-citys-dealing/story?id=28840524" target="_blank"><img class="abc" src="http://briefi.ng/media/abc.svg"></a><a href="http://www.cnn.com/2015/02/10/us/northeast-snow/" target="_blank"><img class="cnn last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/cnn.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row dark" id="s5">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>The House That Dean Built</h1>
<p>University of North Carolina basketball coaching icon Dean Smith died over the weekend. He won 2 national championships and took UNC to 11 Final Fours. Grantland’s Charles Pierce penned an <a href="http://grantland.com/the-triangle/dean-smith-1931-2015-obituary-north-carolina/">obituary</a> for Smith yesterday, a must-read for lovers of sport, life, and memory.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://espn.go.com/mens-college-basketball/story/_/id/12296176/dean-smith-former-north-carolina-tar-heels-coach-dies-age-83" target="_blank"><img class="espn" src="http://briefi.ng/media/espn.svg"></a><a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/02/09/dean-smith-stories_n_6646750.html" target="_blank"><img class="huffpo" src="http://briefi.ng/media/huffpo.svg"></a><a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/on-leadership/wp/2015/02/09/dean-smiths-wisdom-on-leading-teams/" target="_blank"><img class="wapo last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/wapo.svg"></a>
