		<item>
		<title>Trouble for the euro, peace talks in Ukraine and more in today’s Briefing.</title>
		<link>http://briefi.ng/02-09-2015/463</link>
		<comments>http://briefi.ng/02-09-2015/463#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 09 Feb 2015 12:28:49 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[wvnutt]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Daily Briefing]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://briefi.ng/?p=463</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Had Edward Snowden Been a Banker… He probably would’ve been involved in the largest banking leak in history. That’s what they’re calling the HSBC Bank files made public Sunday, except Snowden wasn’t involved. According to documents hacked by a former HSBC IT specialist, the Swiss branch of the bank was complicit in a number of [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="row dark" id="s1">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Had Edward Snowden Been a Banker…</h1>
<p>He probably would’ve been involved in the largest banking leak in history. That’s what they’re calling the HSBC Bank files made public Sunday, except Snowden wasn’t involved.</p>
<p>According to documents hacked by a former HSBC IT specialist, the Swiss branch of the bank was <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/feb/08/hsbc-files-expose-swiss-bank-clients-dodge-taxes-hide-millions">complicit in a number of illegal activities</a>, including allowing clients to withdraw “bricks” of cash in foreign currencies, providing accounts to convicted criminals, and promoting strategies to allow wealthy clients to avoid taxes.</p>
<p>The files are dated between 2005 and 2007, covering more than 30,000 HSBC accounts worth nearly $120 billion. <i>60 Minutes</i> ran a <a href="http://www.cbsnews.com/news/hsbc-swiss-leaks-investigation-60-minutes/">solid segment</a> on the scandal last night.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://money.cnn.com/2015/02/08/news/hsbc-swiss-bank-accounts/" target="_blank"><img class="cnn" src="http://briefi.ng/media/cnn.svg"></a><a href="http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/hsbc-chief-faces-questions-tax-revelations-28826469" target="_blank"><img class="abc" src="http://briefi.ng/media/abc.svg"></a><a href="http://www.npr.org/2015/02/09/384865935/leaked-hsbc-documents-shed-light-on-swiss-banking-industry" target="_blank"><img class="npr last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/npr.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row" id="s2">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Hold the EU</h1>
<p>Greek Prime Minister Alexis Tsipras told the EU to kick rocks Sunday: Tsipras is refusing to stick to conditions tied to the EU’s $272 billion bailout for Greece.</p>
<p>That <a href="http://www.bbc.com/news/business-31249907">could spell doom for the euro</a>, former Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan told the BBC. Greenspan thinks Greece will eventually leave the EU, further undermining the currency (which he’s never liked).</p>
<p>Tsipras’s speech was his first to the Greek Parliament, having been elected in January. The leader of the Coalition of the Radical Left (SYRIZA), Tsipras called the bailout’s stipulations “cruel” and pledged to reinstate government pensions and raise the minimum wage.</p>
<p>EU members, particularly Germany, are <a href="http://blogs.reuters.com/great-debate/2015/02/06/the-communist-manifesto-2015-edition/">none too pleased</a>.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.usatoday.com/story/money/markets/2015/02/09/tsipras-greece-eurozone-debt-payments/23107059/" target="_blank"><img class="usatoday" src="http://briefi.ng/media/usatoday.svg"></a><a href="http://www.wsj.com/articles/greek-leader-tsipras-pledges-to-press-ahead-on-undoing-austerity-measures-1423426204" target="_blank"><img class="wsj" src="http://briefi.ng/media/wsj.svg"></a><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/greek-leader-reject-austerity-lay-hard-leftist-program-121743529--business.html" target="_blank"><img class="yahoo last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/yahoo.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row dark" id="s3">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Peace Talks on Tap</h1>
<p>Russian and Ukrainian leaders will meet Wednesday to discuss a potential peace agreement between the two countries.</p>
<p>Russian President Vladimir Putin and Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko will be joined by German Chancellor Angela Merkel and French President Francois Hollande in Minsk, Belarus.</p>
<p>The fighting in eastern Ukraine between Russian separatists and Ukrainian forces has left more than 5,300 people dead since last April. As recent fighting has grown worse, U.S. calls for military aid on behalf of Ukraine have grown bolder. And that’s forced European leaders to push for a peace deal.</p>
<p>Although the U.S. won’t be party to Wednesday’s negotiations, Merkel <a href="http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/E/EU_UKRAINE_DIPLOMACY?SITE=AP&#038;SECTION=HOME&#038;TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&#038;CTIME=2015-02-08-14-19-17">will be in Washington D.C.</a> today to discuss the issues with President Obama.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/02/09/us/politics/ap-us-obama-merkel.html" target="_blank"><img class="nyt" src="http://briefi.ng/media/nyt.svg"></a><a href="http://www.cnbc.com/id/102407253" target="_blank"><img class="cnbc" src="http://briefi.ng/media/cnbc.svg"></a><a href="http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2015/02/07/384514520/merkel-hopes-to-dissuade-obama-from-arming-ukraine" target="_blank"><img class="npr last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/npr.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row" id="s4">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>There’s A Riot Goin’ On</h1>
<p>At least 25 people were killed at a <a href="http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/S/SOC_EGYPT_SOCCER_RIOT?SITE=AP&#038;SECTION=HOME&#038;TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&#038;CTIME=2015-02-08-17-04-23">soccer riot in Egypt Sunday</a>.</p>
<p>The military-led Egyptian government has been weary of allowing big crowds at soccer games and not because they don&#8217;t like soccer. One group of soccer fans, known as the “Ultras,” is politically active and has been known to clash with police.</p>
<p>Sunday’s riot followed police attempts to channel ticket holders through only one of the stadium’s entrances. Pushing and shoving ensued, and the police responded with teargas.</p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://time.com/3700332/egyptian-soccer-football-cairo-match-riot-stampede/" target="_blank"><img class="time" src="http://briefi.ng/media/time.svg"></a><a href="http://sports.yahoo.com/news/official-least-5-dead-egypt-soccer-riot-toll-194644703--sow.html;_ylt=AwrBJSAjothUqjIA2ZHQtDMD" target="_blank"><img class="yahoo" src="http://briefi.ng/media/yahoo.svg"></a><a href="http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2015/02/08/official-at-least-5-dead-in-egypt-soccer-riot-toll-to-rise/23082259/" target="_blank"><img class="usatoday last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/usatoday.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
               </div>
<div class="row dark" id="s5">
<div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-lg-6 col-lg-offset-3">
<h1>Cutting the Cake?</h1>
<p>Alabama is slated to begin issuing gay marriage licenses today, but Roy Moore, Chief Justice of the state’s supreme court, isn’t exactly thrilled.</p>
<p>Moore <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/09/us/gay-marriage-set-to-begin-in-alabama-amid-protest.html">sent an order</a> to Alabama probate judges Sunday, saying they shouldn’t issue the licenses. Although a federal judge ruled in January that Alabama’s gay marriage ban was unconstitutional, Moore said the probate judges don’t have to abide.</p>
<p>Pro-gay rights groups believe Moore’s efforts will fail. If so, Alabama <a href="http://www.npr.org/2015/02/09/384852553/alabama-chief-justice-tells-probate-judges-to-refuse-same-sex-marriage-licenses">will become the 37th state</a> where gays can cut the cake.</p>
<p class="background"><a href="http://briefi.ng/gay-marriage-map">Marriage Map &rarr;</a></p>
<div class="line"></div>
<div class="media-logos">
                        <a href="http://www.cbsnews.com/news/alabama-gay-marriage-chief-justice-roy-moore-judges-ignore-federal-court/" target="_blank"><img class="cbsnews" src="http://briefi.ng/media/cbsnews.svg"></a><a href="http://www.npr.org/2015/02/09/384852553/alabama-chief-justice-tells-probate-judges-to-refuse-same-sex-marriage-licenses?utm_medium=RSS&#038;utm_campaign=storiesfromnpr" target="_blank"><img class="npr" src="http://briefi.ng/media/npr.svg"></a><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/09/us/gay-marriage-set-to-begin-in-alabama-amid-protest.html" target="_blank"><img class="nyt last" src="http://briefi.ng/media/nyt.svg"></a>
                      </div>
<p><!-- /.media-logos -->
                    </div>
<p><!-- /col -->
